	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi all, I am not a very avid EQ player.  I play maybe 8 hours a week, at the most, and my main just hit 20.  I have been playing on and off for almost two years.  Hold the laughs please :p But, I love my SK, I started a Dwarven Pally first, he was ok, then a DE war, and I really liked him.  Though, was hard to RP the DE, cuz I needed friends, so couldn't be the stuck-up I hate everyone jerk :p  But, my SK rocks... soloing yellows at 20!?! Awesome! So what if the druids can do it(not flaming here).  I don't train them around the zone.  I Clinging Darkness them, run away a bit, Syphon Strength them, sick my pet, fear them(he can take like 3 or 4 hits, then we chase him down, beating on his back. I Lifespike in between, and cling darkness when he starts to run.  Game over for him :p  Usually lose about a bub and a half, maybe two in life, and half mana.  Some down time, but fun :)  I can also RP, cuz I don't need anyone else :p I can be mean, and still survive.  My pet rocks to, he can bash, to interrupt spels, and his attacks interuppt, and he does like 10 dam per tick :p That's a decent DOT for my level :)  Wait until he levels up at 22 :)  All this is based off of my experience in Oasis, and Timorous deep.  Adds suck, that's the bad part :(  Druids rock, teamed with a druid, I can't be beaten :) But I am just of a more Toe-to-Toe guy myself.  Anyway, that's my idea, wish I had time to elaborate, but at work :p  Later all.<br><br>Morchai<br>20 Dark Elf Shadow-knight of Innoruuk.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
